          <avActivityHighlights>Considerable avalanche danger will prevail. &lt;br/&gt; The wind slabs represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>The avalanche prone locations are to be found adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls and at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack. Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground. They can in many places be released, even by a single winter sport participant.  Wooded areas could also be affected by avalanches and present situations of instability. Moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The weather conditions gave rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack. &lt;br/&gt; The wind slabs of the last few days are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. Precarious weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>The weather will be cloudy. Over a wide area light snowfall.</tendencyComment>
